    <h3>Is an AMC Worth It?</h3>
    <p>For ovens valued above ₹1,50,000, a comprehensive AMC almost always makes financial sense when you factor in:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Avoided unplanned repair costs (one major repair — a fan motor, control board, or rotation mechanism — can exceed the full AMC cost)</li>
      <li>Scheduled maintenance prevents the compounding failures that happen when minor issues are missed</li>
      <li>Production continuity — faster response time vs hunting for a random technician in an emergency</li>
      <li>Warranty protection — many manufacturers require documented maintenance to honour warranty claims</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For a basic countertop convection oven worth ₹40,000–₹70,000, an AMC may not be cost-effective. Build a relationship with a local technician and do your own daily and weekly maintenance instead.</p>

    <h2>Section 6: Spare Parts Availability in India</h2>

    <p>Spare parts availability is one of the most important — and most underestimated — factors when buying a commercial oven in India. A European oven with no local parts stock can sit idle for 3–6 weeks waiting for a heating element to clear customs. An Indian or Taiwanese-brand oven may have parts available in your city within 24 hours.</p>

